http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Heated-arguments-between-Congress-BJP/article13977852.ece

There were heated arguments between the Congress and the Bharatiya Janata Party over alleged inefficiency in implementing drinking water projects and delay in releasing compensation to families of those farmers who committed suicide, at the Yadgir Zilla Panchayat general body meeting on Saturday.The meeting was chaired by president Sharanamma Sahukar while vice-president Hanumegowda Markal, Chief Executive Officer Vikas Suralkar were present.Officials of the National Rural Drinking Water and Sanitation Division, who brought the notice of the house about the drinking water project, have said that 1,057 drinking projects had been taken up at a cost of Rs. 6,457 lakh for 2015-16. Of them, 937 projects were completed by spending Rs. 1,263 lakh and the remaining would be completed at the earliest.Chetana Patil, Joint Director, Agriculture Department, has said that crops on 2.20 lakh hectares of 2.92 lakh hectares area, covered under Kharif season, were damaged due to moisture stress and detailed reports had been sent to the State government to release compensation.As many as 46 farmers committed suicide owing to crop loss and compensation of Rs. 5 lakh each to 27 families of those farmers had been released and 10 cases are before the committee headed by the Assistant Commissioner of Yadgir sub-division for further action.The Health and Family Welfare Department has prepared an action plan to take up several projects including installing generators, surgery equipments and other infrastructures to the hospitals at the cost of Rs. 3 crore.